{
  "texts": [
    "In Sect. 4.4, we discuss in more detail the follow-up requirements for lensed SNe.",
    "Lensed SNe are powerful astrophysical tools to study supernovae and galaxies, in addition to probing cosmology through their time delays.",
    "In Sect. 3.1, we explain how lensed SNe provide an excellent opportunity to constrain SN progenitors.",
    "In Sect. 3.2, we describe how lensing magnifications enable the acquisition of high-redshift SN spectra that are crucial for SN cosmology.",
    "In Sect. 3.3, we outline the use of microlensing to probe SN structure."
  ]
}